review_blob: cask conditioned , the crown , huddersfield , served in tulip pint glass. Pours a port wine colour, with a fruity berry flavor. Slightly bitter after taste. Nice tight white head with slight blue tinge. Very pleasant , if unusual looking ale .
served in tulip pint glass , cherry tree huddersfield. Pleasent sweet creamy stout, jet black colour with tight biege head
served in tulip glass , cherry tree huddersfild. dark red , slightly hoppy ale , leaves good lacing on glass .

severed in tulip glass, poured without sparkler, cherry tree(jdw) huddersfield. Jet black beer with light bron head, smokey flavor, not dissimilar to German rauch beer. Hints of coffee and liqorice also present
Served in tulip glass, at the cherry tree (jdw)huddersfield, nice orange-gold colour, acceptable strong hoppy bitter, but not as powerful flavor as the keg version from the usa
Served in tulip pint glass, at the parish,(huddersfield). Hoppy American style pale ale. Nice dark gold colour
bought in 33cl bottle in vox bar, huddersfield, served in branded delirium glass. Beautiful dark red colour, cherry led fruit flavour, drinks far to easy for a beer of this strength ,

Chilled 330mls bottle , served in branded peroni 1/2 pt glass. Pale yellow lager , with fluffy white head , sulphury , damp cardboard aroma , inoffensive flavor, typical Mediterranean beer, ie cold and wet , not a beer to sip and savor . Not the worst lager Ive had , but not the best .

bought as sainsburys English vintage cider (2014) , 750ml bottle, sainsburys morecambe. Served chilled in straight glass. Nice bitter sweet apple with subtle oaked flavor, with smoky under tones. No head ( it is cider after all ), but nice gold colour. Fresh apple aroma, nicely sparkling .

Bought at sainsburys , morecambe, served lightly chilled in duvel glass. Massive white head on top of hazy pale beer . Slightly herby citrus flavor, (not dissimilar to a saison) with a slightly bitter after taste.

500ml bottle bought in tesco huddersfield. Served in straight glass . Bitter-sweet apple taste , nice apple aroma, good straw gold colour , no head. Easy drinking, does not drink like a 8.2 % . (2014 vintage).
beer_name: Westons Henry Westons Vintage Reserve Cider

review_blob: 330mls bottle, bought in co-op supermarket , huddersfield. Served in large goblet glass. Dark gold colour with big white foam head. Slightly syrupy , breakfast cereal flavor. Not too fizzy, with lightly bitter after taste .
served in tulip pint glass, hand pulled ,cherry tree (jdw), huddersfield. Slightly sulphury aroma, hazy amber beer with tight head . Left good lace on glass, disappointing overall.
served in tulip pint glass, hand pulled at cherry tree (jdw), huddersfield. Slightly hazy pale ale, slightly citrus hop flavor, golden colour , not as good as i was expecting.

served in straight pint glass , cherry tree (jdw), huddersfield. Packed with esspresso and liqorice flavours , thick dark beer with creamy head, roasted aroma, a beer to sip and savour , in a word , awesome .

served in straight pint glass, at vox bar , huddersfield . Hoppy , American style pale ale, slightly fizzy keg beer , good flavor, wet hop aroma. Amber colour , with white head which collapsed quite quickly.

can from co-op supermarket, drank at home, in 12 fl oz scooner. inoffensive beer, nice amber colour, creamy head, malty, slightly sweet caramel flavor. Remember this (original S&N; version) as the beer available on British rail in the 1980s, not as bad a expected,
